Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.33,0:00:18.75,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Home at last...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.75,0:00:20.72,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Waver!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.28,0:00:24.24,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking at? \NOver here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.24,0:00:25.87,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,G-Grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.87,0:00:27.21,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.21,0:00:29.23,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.23,0:00:30.96,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Come on up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.96,0:00:32.87,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I wanna talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.87,0:00:36.46,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be on the roof again?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.12,0:00:39.56,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, could we talk later?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.56,0:00:42.06,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, come on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.45,0:00:46.06,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,He likes you, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.90,0:00:49.72,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That's just because I hypnotized him—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.30,0:00:52.29,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, go on...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.29,0:00:56.07,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,That old fellow seems like \Nhe really wants to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.79,0:01:00.37,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hang around and keep \Nan eye on things, so relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:02.13,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,No need to be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.60,0:01:04.49,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,It's not about being shy...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.85,0:02:43.55,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,This here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:47.92,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,...is the best spot to watch the sun rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:52.06,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:56.07,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I made coffee,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.07,0:02:57.64,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,so warm yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.64,0:03:00.81,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Grandpa, how long have you been up here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.81,0:03:05.56,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I woke up early in the morning\N and you still hadn't come home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.56,0:03:11.58,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought I'd watch the sky\Nand wait for my grandson to come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.38,0:03:16.58,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,We used to stargaze
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.58,0:03:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this way all the time when you were little...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.15,0:03:22.58,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.79,0:03:25.78,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.78,0:03:28.73,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,When Martha and I decided to live in Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.73,0:03:31.69,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,we built our house here on Miyama Hill
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:36.05,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,and made sure to include a skylight \Nthat allowed access to the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:40.20,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,And all so we could sit out here, \Nlike we're doing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.20,0:03:43.28,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,That was our old dream, to stargaze on the roof,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:45.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,next to our grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.85,0:03:48.85,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Never thought it'd come true, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:54.00,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Our real grandchildren
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.00,0:03:57.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,never once came up here with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.71,0:04:02.50,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I've always watched the stars all by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.36,0:04:06.22,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Waver...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.73,0:04:09.97,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't our real grandson, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.78,0:04:18.59,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not exactly sure why
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.59,0:04:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Martha and I were so convinced you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:24.87,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, you've always been a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.87,0:04:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,too nice to be one of ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.33,0:04:33.83,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Are you angry?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.83,0:04:38.42,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I have the right to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:43.84,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,But lately, I've been seeing \NMartha smiling cheerfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.14,0:04:46.63,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I never would've imagined it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.63,0:04:49.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I'm grateful to you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.85,0:04:54.80,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I can tell from the look of you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.80,0:04:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you don't mean us any harm by living here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.05,0:05:01.81,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.61,0:05:08.28,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like it if you could stick \Naround for a while longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.25,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.60,0:05:15.39,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't promise that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.39,0:05:18.25,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,There's no guarantee I'll even \Nmake it back alive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.25,0:05:22.11,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,So, the two of you are risking your lives?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.11,0:05:23.26,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.81,0:05:26.07,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know what \Ncould be so important
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you'd be willing to die for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:33.10,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,But when you've lived as long as I have,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.10,0:05:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you take a moment to consider your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:41.68,Default,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,you realize that really, nothing out \Nthere is worth more than it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.21,0:05:59.42,Sign22A,Gramp,0000,0000,0000,,Enzousan
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:04.42,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,Forty hours since I last slept.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.01,0:06:08.23,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,To win the war and call forth the Grail,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.23,0:06:11.28,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,the ceremony must be \Nperformed at one of Fuyuki's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.28,0:06:13.93,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,four major spiritual ley lines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.93,0:06:15.71,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,Two of them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.71,0:06:17.94,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,are the Tohsaka estate and \Nthe Fuyuki City church,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.94,0:06:20.44,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,and there was no sign of Kotomine Kirei at either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.07,0:06:22.69,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,That leaves two places.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.69,0:06:26.69,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,Enzousan and the Fuyuki City civic center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.17,0:06:30.41,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,In terms of spiritual energy, \Nthis location is the obvious choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.41,0:06:32.47,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,On the off-chance he selects the civic center,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:35.43,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,I need only mount a direct assault.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.21,0:06:38.82,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,If Maiya were still alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.82,0:06:41.38,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,I'd have stationed her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.51,0:06:48.37,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm alone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.65,0:06:56.03,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,Actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.58,0:06:59.17,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,I've never thought to count her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.45,0:07:07.66,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Since last night, I have scoured \Nevery inch of the city,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.66,0:07:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,looking for Irisviel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.22,0:07:11.36,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,But I have found nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.84,0:07:14.46,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,I am very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:22.98,Default,Saber,0000,0000,0000,,Should anything happen, \Nplease summon me
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.98,0:07:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with the Command Spells, as you did before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.49,0:07:39.70,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.05,0:07:44.02,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Can you hear me, woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.14,0:07:51.28,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine Kirei...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.28,0:07:56.16,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,This is the place where \NCaster's Master once hid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.96,0:08:01.16,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Kiritsugu never managed to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:04.66,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,The Holy Grail War will soon be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.66,0:08:10.17,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,It appears that I will be given the opportunity\N to grant the Einzbern family wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.33,0:08:13.93,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Are you upset that it would be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.31,0:08:17.18,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I would only relinquish the \NHoly Grail to one man...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.88,0:08:21.93,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,And that is not you, Executor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:26.43,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Kiritsugu sees right through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:30.53,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,He knows you are the opponent to fear most.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.53,0:08:31.94,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Be ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.94,0:08:34.74,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,That is good news indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.23,0:08:40.79,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Kiritsugu is exactly \Nthe man I thought him to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.79,0:08:42.75,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Ridiculous...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.37,0:08:46.63,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,You are further from him than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.52,0:08:48.75,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:51.97,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Kiritsugu can see through you,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.97,0:08:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you can never say the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.39,0:08:57.13,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Your heart has none of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.13,0:08:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he carries within his.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.63,0:09:03.23,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you speak about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:06.50,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I admit it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:09.06,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I am an empty man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.06,0:09:11.94,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,How are he and I different?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.94,0:09:15.70,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,He's subjected himself to fighting endless, \Npointless battles,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:19.30,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,doing nothing but slaughtering \Nothers again and again...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.30,0:09:21.83,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,To live so aimlessly, wasting so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:24.12,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,What are we, if not lost?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.59,0:09:31.01,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.01,0:09:34.67,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,What will Emiya Kiritsugu \Nask of the Holy Grail?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.97,0:09:39.18,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,What wish will he entrust to the \Nsole device that can grant it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.36,0:09:45.63,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.63,0:09:46.94,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.63,0:09:50.69,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Kiritsugu's wish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:53.87,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,is for humanity's salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.87,0:09:57.57,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,An end to war and bloodshed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:09:59.70,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.71,0:10:02.63,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,World peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.30,0:10:09.83,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.59,0:10:13.09,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,You will never understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.09,0:10:15.62,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,And that is how you two differ...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.08,0:10:17.97,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,He has convictions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.26,0:10:23.89,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Human nature is conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.13,0:10:29.98,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,To reject that is to reject humanity itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.60,0:10:33.48,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,It is a baseless ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.96,0:10:36.39,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Like the idle wish of a child!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.39,0:10:41.62,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,And that is why he knows \Nonly a miracle can make it happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.35,0:10:45.71,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,He's been forced to discard \Neveryone he's ever loved,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.64,0:10:50.62,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,in order to make his ideals reality...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.17,0:10:53.13,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.50,0:10:56.80,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Kiritsugu is too kind for his ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:00.63,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Even though he knows he will lose them,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.63,0:11:03.54,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,he cannot stop loving others...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.80,0:11:06.52,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.60,0:11:39.08,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I understand completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.08,0:11:41.63,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,So that is who Emiya Kiritsugu is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.09,0:11:51.27,Default - italic,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Finally, I have a reason to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.94,0:11:55.70,Default - italic,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Emiya Kiritsugu...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.70,0:11:57.45,Default - italic,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall destroy
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.99,0:12:00.52,Default - italic,,0000,0000,0000,,the Holy Grail before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.52,0:12:03.14,Default - italic,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,And with it, your ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.52,0:12:29.81,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you're awake, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.15,0:12:32.94,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I told you to wake me at nightfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.94,0:12:34.56,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.56,0:12:36.77,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.77,0:12:39.78,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I thought tonight we'd be better off
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.78,0:12:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,staying calm and fully preparing ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.84,0:12:43.70,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.09,0:12:47.10,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.80,0:12:51.83,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But my gut says that everything \Nwill be decided tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.21,0:12:56.33,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the night air feels too still.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.38,0:13:00.63,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Is it because there are fewer of us left?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.09,0:13:09.85,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,From here on out, it will be only \Nthe powerful adversaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.39,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,W-What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.88,0:13:19.16,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,A strange mana burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:21.61,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I've felt something similar before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.15,0:13:28.70,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,That pattern...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.70,0:13:29.74,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:31.41,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Some manner of code?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.41,0:13:33.74,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Four of one color, seven of another...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.04,0:13:35.86,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,"Achieved" and "victory."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.86,0:13:37.79,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,The signal is pretty clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.55,0:13:42.05,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean the Holy Grail \NWar's already been decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:46.78,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,No, the church is in the complete opposite direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.30,0:13:49.74,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Then the church didn't fire those...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.26,0:13:51.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds to me
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.56,0:13:55.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,like someone's getting ahead of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.57,0:13:59.51,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,"If you don't like it, \Nshow yourself."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.51,0:14:01.57,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,We're being challenged.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.12,0:14:05.32,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,This is the beginning of the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.05,0:14:08.18,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.18,0:14:11.20,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.40,0:14:12.74,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.10,0:14:14.08,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.08,0:14:17.04,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,If our battlefield has been decided,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.04,0:14:20.89,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I must comport myself so as not to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.89,0:14:23.30,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,bring shame upon the Rider class!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.51,0:14:25.60,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Come forth,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.14,0:14:27.72,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,my faithful steed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.98,0:14:35.58,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.58,0:14:38.62,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,It will be a rougher ride than the chariot...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:41.96,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,What are you waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.96,0:14:42.57,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Get on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.33,0:14:48.45,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Only the powerful can continue...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:55.15,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,My Servant...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.15,0:14:58.16,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I, Waver Velvet, order you\N with this Command Spell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:02.42,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Rider, you must be victorious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.48,0:15:07.77,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,With this Command Spell, I order you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.77,0:15:10.68,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Rider, you must obtain the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.52,0:15:15.76,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,And by my Command Spell, I order you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.07,0:15:18.32,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Rider, you must conquer this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.32,0:15:20.15,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Failure will not be tolerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.27,0:15:28.65,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,There, I'm no longer your Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:31.41,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.41,0:15:33.16,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Go wherever you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.83,0:15:36.56,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You're just...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.57,0:15:42.42,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,I shall go in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:45.56,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,But after issuing all those long-winded orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.56,0:15:48.30,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,surely you're prepared to watch \Nme carry them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.30,0:15:49.77,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, no, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.77,0:15:52.09,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Look, I have no Command Spells.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:53.71,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I quit being a Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.71,0:15:55.43,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you take me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:57.64,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.93,0:15:59.96,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You may no longer be my Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.96,0:16:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you are certainly my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:10.05,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I-I am...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.48,0:16:13.06,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't mind a kid like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.47,0:16:16.07,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,You'd let me come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.07,0:16:20.70,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,After all the battles we have fought \Ntogether, how can you ask that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.70,0:16:21.65,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.74,0:16:27.64,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,We have faced every enemy as partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.64,0:16:29.34,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,You are my friend!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:31.47,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Stand tall, and consider yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.35,0:16:34.34,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,my equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.13,0:16:44.48,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, I shall begin with your first order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.77,0:16:47.23,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Watch closely and I shall fulfill it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.87,0:16:52.36,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,Go get them...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.69,0:16:54.83,Default,Waver,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.37,0:17:16.34,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,He chose the worst possible \Nsite for the ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.34,0:17:19.62,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,to control when and where \Nthe fights commence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.32,0:17:24.52,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he doesn't \Nwant the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:28.02,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to use it as bait, to lure and kill
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.78,0:17:32.59,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,the other Masters and me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.29,0:17:38.20,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,That makes things simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.20,0:17:40.60,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the best he can come up with,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.47,0:17:44.04,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,I must make it quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.63,0:17:48.43,Default - italic,Kiri,0000,0000,0000,,Kotomine Kirei...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.84,0:17:58.74,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,You do look especially ferocious tonight,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.74,0:17:59.85,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.14,0:18:03.26,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,What do you plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.26,0:18:05.60,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Shall I stay here and wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.05,0:18:09.13,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Unleashing your power at close range
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.13,0:18:11.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would put the ceremony at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.33,0:18:16.26,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to fight at full strength, \Nthen go out and welcome them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.26,0:18:17.63,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:20.28,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,But what if you're attacked while I'm away?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.75,0:18:24.54,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I will summon you with a Command Spell, \Nif you would indulge me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.54,0:18:26.05,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,That would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.05,0:18:29.14,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,But I make no guarantees \Nfor the Grail's safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.14,0:18:31.79,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, I shall not hold back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.05,0:18:34.23,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,That is the worst-case scenario,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.23,0:18:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if it happens, then that is fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.25,0:18:42.05,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Kirei, you seem to have found \Nyour reason to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.42,0:18:45.68,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, have you still no \Nprayer to offer the Grail?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.38,0:18:49.61,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,No, I cannot think of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.14,0:18:55.76,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,If forced, I would say I wish for no one\N to interfere with this fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:57.89,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Really, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.89,0:19:00.28,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,As I thought, the only thing to do
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.28,0:19:03.69,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,is to let the Grail draw out \Nwhat you have hidden in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.47,0:19:12.17,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,If it seems that Saber will \Narrive before I return,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.17,0:19:15.21,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,let Berserker keep her occupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.05,0:19:17.72,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.07,0:19:19.76,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of Saber,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:23.22,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,what became of the puppet she \Nprotected so desperately?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.68,0:19:28.04,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Is not the Holy Grail's vessel inside of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:30.63,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.14,0:19:34.01,Default,Kirei,0000,0000,0000,,There was no reason to let her live.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.38,0:20:02.18,Default,Ilya,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.02,0:20:04.51,Default,Ilya,0000,0000,0000,,Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.89,0:20:08.63,Default,Ilya,0000,0000,0000,,Mother, I had a bad dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.63,0:20:11.02,Default,Ilya,0000,0000,0000,,I dreamed I turned into a cup...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:13.27,Default,Ilya,0000,0000,0000,,And inside me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.27,0:20:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were these big lumps, seven of them...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.92,0:20:19.53,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, it's okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.13,0:20:22.57,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never let that happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.57,0:20:25.53,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I promise that it won't happen, Ilya.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.16,0:20:31.69,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I know that you'll be freed \Nfrom the bonds of fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.61,0:20:49.66,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Where...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:53.94,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the Holy Grail?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:55.83,Default,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.71,0:21:05.95,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.95,0:21:11.12,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I here?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.83,0:21:28.39,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.84,0:21:31.00,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I'm inside the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.46,0:21:35.39,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,The omnipotent wish-granting artifact that \Nwill wash away the world's sorrows,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.33,0:21:38.62,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,and end its suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.01,0:21:41.37,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,I will have the power to \Nmake that all come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.57,0:21:43.79,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,The end...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.22,0:21:47.31,Default - italic,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,is close at hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.04,0:21:55.04,Title,Iri,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 22: \NAll the Evil in the World
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.48,0:23:28.31,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Our opponent is the mighty \NKing of Heroes,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.31,0:23:30.45,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,a truly worthy foe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.45,0:23:33.30,Default,Rider,0000,0000,0000,,Let us show him where our \Npath of conquest leads!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.30,0:23:36.99,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,King of Conquerors, I shall wake \Nyou from your endless dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.99,0:23:39.66,Default,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,I shall see to it personally.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.52,0:23:40.01,Title,Arch,0000,0000,0000,,Next Time: \NThe Ocean at the End of the World
